{"id":"1306.3676","submitter":"Dmitri Yafaev","authors":"D. R. Yafaev","title":"Diagonalizations of two classes of unbounded Hankel operators","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.FA math.SP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We show that every Hankel operator $H$ is unitarily equivalent to a\npseudo-differential operator $A$ of a special structure acting in the space\n$L^2 ({\\Bbb R}) $. As an example, we consider integral operators $H$ in the\nspace $L^2 ({\\Bbb R}_{+}) $ with kernels $P (\\ln (t+s)) (t+s)^{-1}$ where\n$P(x)$ is an arbitrary real polynomial of degree $K$. In this case, $A$ is a\ndifferential operator of the same order $K$. This allows us to study spectral\nproperties of Hankel operators $H$ with such kernels. In particular, we show\nthat the essential spectrum of $H$ coincides with the whole axis for $K$ odd,\nand it coincides with the positive half-axis for $K$ even. In the latter case\nwe additionally find necessary and sufficient conditions for the positivity of\n$H$. We also consider Hankel operators whose kernels have a strong singularity\nat some positive point. We show that spectra of such operators consist of the\nzero eigenvalue of infinite multiplicity and eigenvalues accumulating to\n$+\\infty$ and $-\\infty$. We find the asymptotics of these eigenvalues.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 16 Jun 2013 16:28:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-06-18"}
