cal lens parameters. This\ndemonstrates the importance of routine consideration of orbital effects in\ninterpreting light curves of binary-lens events. It is found that the lens of\nOGLE-2006-BLG-277 is a binary composed of a low-mass star and a brown dwarf\ncompanion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 17 Jun 2013 06:27:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-16"}
